Cite 16 U.S.C. Ã¯Â¿Â½ 1538(c) 16 U.S.C. Ã¯Â¿Â½ 3372 National Marine Sanctuaries Prohibits the destruction, injury or possession of any sanctuary resources (defined as any living or nonliving resource of a national marine sanctuary that contributes to the conservation, recreational, ecological, historical, research, educational, or aesthetic value of the sanctuary) in a national marine sanctuary.
