In Biscayne National Park, a recent aerial survey revealed that many of Biscayne Bay's seagrass flats have already had as much as 20% of the seagrass destroyed by propeller scarring and vessel groundings (BNP report, citing Sargent et al. 1995).
In Biscayne NP, seagrass grounding numbers are considered to be only 20% of all groundings.
United States Coral Reef Task Force Coastal Uses Working Group Summary Report -94Groundings on coral reefs go unreported because rarely do vessels become stranded as a result of grounding on a reef.
As a result, damages to coral reefs caused by vessel groundings may remain undiscovered and unrestored.
Fish and Wildlife Service (DOI/FWS) National Wildife Refuges with tropical coral reef resources include Great Heron NWR, Key West NWR in South Florida, and Hawai`ian Islands NWR, Midway Atoll NWR, Johnston Atoll NWR, Howland Island NWR, Baker Island NWR, Rose Atoll NWR, Jarvis Island NWR, and Guam NWR in the Pacific.
