CERCLA, 42 U.S.C. 9601 et seq.
Owner or operator of vessel, or generator or transporter of hazardous wastes is liable for response costs and damages for hazardous substance releases.
Ã¯Â¿Â½9607.
EPA/Coast Guard may perform removal actions to address pollutant or contaminant releases.
Creates liability to U.S, states, or tribes for natural resource damage from hazardous substance releases, with any recovered sums to be used for restoration, replacement or acquisition of natural resources by federal, state, or tribal trustees.
Federal trustees include NOAA, DOI, USDA, DOD, and DOE.
Authorizes the President to clean up hazardous substances, pollutants, or contaminants in order to protect public health or the environment.
Ã¯Â¿Â½9604(a).
